This paper deals with a problem in distributed robotics, specifically with mobile robots operating in a two-dimensional plane. The paper discusses the solvability of a new class of problems related to permutations of the robots' locations, which is a topic that falls under the scope of robotics and distributed computing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics), followed by cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.MA (Multiagent Systems).
